0. READ-ITEM ARRAY-IN ARRAY-OUT
1. COMPARE ARRAY-IN(0) TO ARRAY-IN(1) ; IF GREATER GO TO 4, IF EQUAL GO TO 2, OTHERWISE GO TO 2
2. TRANSFER ARRAY-IN TO WORKING-AREA
3. WRITE-ITEM WORKING-AREA
4. STOP
;
; FLOW-MATIC approximation of pancake sort
; FLOW-MATIC was the precursor to COBOL, designed by Grace Hopper
; It operated on records and files, not arrays directly
; The algorithm concept:
; 0. READ INPUT RECORD
; 1. FIND MAXIMUM IN UNSORTED PORTION
; 2. IF MAXIMUM NOT AT FRONT, REVERSE PREFIX TO BRING TO FRONT
; 3. REVERSE ENTIRE UNSORTED PORTION TO MOVE MAX TO END
; 4. REDUCE UNSORTED PORTION SIZE BY ONE
; 5. IF MORE TO SORT, GO TO 1
; 6. WRITE OUTPUT RECORD
; 7. STOP
